MEADOW LAKE WIND FARM VI LLC
RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Meadow Lake Wind Farm VI LLC ("Meadow Lake VI") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Meadow Lake V generating facility ("Meadow Lake VI Facility").
The Meadow Lake VI Facility is a wind turbine generating facility located in Benton and White Counties, Indiana. The Meadow Lake VI Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities owned by Indiana Michigan Power Company and under the operational control of the PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM").
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Meadow Lake VI's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Meadow Lake VI Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
Meadow Lake VI's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to Meadow Lake VI shall be subject to Schedule 2 of PJM's Open Access Transmission Tariff.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT: The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $570,000.00. The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $47,500.00.
